25 general election.The registered voters of a school district may refer a resolution adopted
26 by the board of a school district to implement a school sentinel program, pursuant to § 13-
27 64-1, by filing with the business manager of the school district, a petition signed by at
28 least five percent of the registered voters of the school district, based upon the total
29 number of registered voters in the school district at the last preceding general election,
30 within forty-five thirty days of the adoption of the resolution.
31 The board shall allow sufficient time for the referendum process authorized in this
32 section.
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

1323A 14 1323
1 Section 15. That § 7-18A-15.1 be REPEALED.
2 Any legislative decision of a board of county commissioners is subject to the
3 referendum process. A legislative decision is one that enacts a permanent law or lays
4 down a rule of conduct or course of policy for the guidance of citizens or their officers. Any
5 matter of a permanent or general character is a legislative decision.
6 No administrative decision of a governing body is subject to the referendum
7 process, unless specifically authorized by this code. An administrative decision is one that
8 merely puts into execution a plan already adopted by the governing body itself or by the
9 Legislature. Supervision of a program is an administrative decision. Hiring, disciplining,
10 and setting the salaries of employees are administrative decisions.
11 Section 16. That § 7-18A-16 be REPEALED.
12 A petition to refer an ordinance or resolution subject to referendum may be filed
13 with the auditor within twenty days after publication of the ordinance or resolution in the
14 last to publish official county newspaper. The filing of the petition requires the submission
15 of the ordinance or resolution to a vote of the qualified voters of the county for rejection
16 or approval of the ordinance or resolution.
17 Section 17. That § 13-26-10 be REPEALED.
18 A petition to refer a school board decision may be filed with the business manager
19 of the school district within twenty days after its publication. The filing of the petition shall
20 require the submission of the decision to a vote of the qualified voters of the school district
21 for its rejection or approval.
22 Section 18. That § 13-64-8 be REPEALED.
23 A petition to refer a school board decision pursuant to § 13-64-7 may be filed with
24 the business manager of the school district within twenty days after its publication. The
25 filing of the petition shall require the submission of the decision to a vote of the qualified
26 voters of the school district for its rejection or approval.
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

